  <scopecontent id="aspace_63a18a46e32e45b9f9aef2f571c6dfc9">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Architectural drawings and abstract of title, history and pledge class scrapbooks. Also chapter bylaws, 2002.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_9bb72d27befb0301fb974ce7bfcae097">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Pi Beta Phi, New York Delta chapter records, #37-4-3271. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <accessrestrict audience="internal" id="aspace_52c52bab326bb82ecbd6a6f001ea10eb">
    <head>Access Restrictions:</head>
<p>Access restricted to current members and alumnae of Pi Beta Phi Sorority, NY Delta Chapter (Pi Beta Phi provides and updates a list of active members.  Photo ID is required.) Or by permission from the New York Delta Chapter President and the Vice President of Fraternity Development, either in person, by signed letter, or email.</p>  </accessrestrict>
  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_33b7282906b058d5b715de6702f30169">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>The New York Delta chapter of Pi Beta Phi was founded at Cornell University in 1919.</p>  </bioghist>
